kilometers had been covered. The physical motion that was employed by the runner was \textit{jogging}. The time it took to cover the distance was calculated using the following code snippet:

\begin{verbatim}
distance = 15 - 10
speed = 8 # kilometers per hour
time = distance / speed
\end{verbatim}

The time it took to reach the station was approximately \textbf{0.625 hours}.

